{"title_page": "Manfred Purzer", "text_new": "{{short description|German screenwriter}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| image        =\n| name         = Manfred Purzer\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|1931|4|13|df=yes}}\n| birth_place  = [[Munich]], Germany\n| death_date   =\n| death_place  =\n| occupation   = [[Screenwriter]]<br>[[Film director]]\n| yearsactive  = 1955-1993\n}}\n\n'''Manfred Purzer''' (born 13 April 1931) is a German [[screenwriter]] and [[film director]]. He wrote 27 films between 1955 and 1993. In 1974, he was a member of the jury at the [[24th Berlin International Film Festival]].<ref name=\"berlinale\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.berlinale.de/en/archiv/jahresarchive/1974/04_jury_1974/04_Jury_1974.html |title=Berlinale 1974: Juries |accessdate=2 July 2010 |work=berlinale.de}}</ref>\n\n==Selected filmography==\n===Screenwriter===\n* ''{{ill|Komm nur, mein liebstes V\u00f6gelein|de}}'' (dir. [[Rolf Thiele]], 1968) \u2014 based on a book by {{Ill|Joachim Fernau|de}}\n* ''[[Seven Days Grace]]'' (dir. [[Alfred Vohrer]], 1969) \u2014 based on a novel by {{Ill|Paul Henricks|de}}\n* ''{{Ill|Herzblatt oder Wie sag ich\u2019s meiner Tochter?|de}}'' (dir. [[Alfred Vohrer]], 1969)\n* ''[[The Sex Nest]]'' (dir. [[Alfred Vohrer]], 1970) \u2014 based on a novel by {{Ill|Bengta Bischoff|de}}\n* ''{{Ill|Perrak|de}}'' (dir. [[Alfred Vohrer]], 1970)\n* ''{{ill|Die Weibchen|de}}'' (dir. [[Zbyn\u011bk Brynych]], 1970)\n* ''[[Und Jimmy ging zum Regenbogen]]'' (dir. [[Alfred Vohrer]], 1971) \u2014 based on a novel by [[Johannes Mario Simmel]]\n* ''{{ill|Der neue hei\u00dfe Sex-Report \u2013 Was M\u00e4nner nicht f\u00fcr m\u00f6glich halten|de}}'' (dir. [[Ernst Hofbauer]], 1971)\n* ''[[Love Is Only a Word]]'' (dir. [[Alfred Vohrer]], 1971) \u2014 based on a novel by [[Johannes Mario Simmel]]\n* ''[[The Stuff That Dreams Are Made Of (film)|The Stuff That Dreams Are Made Of]]'' (dir. [[Alfred Vohrer]], 1972) \u2014 based on a novel by [[Johannes Mario Simmel]]\n* ''[[Tears of Blood]]'' (dir. [[Alfred Vohrer]], 1972) \u2014 based on ''[[The Blizzard]]'' by [[Alexander Pushkin]]\n* ''[[All People Will Be Brothers]]'' (dir. [[Alfred Vohrer]], 1973) \u2014 based on a novel by [[Johannes Mario Simmel]]\n*''{{Ill|Gott sch\u00fctzt die Liebenden|de|Gott sch\u00fctzt die Liebenden (1973)}}'' (dir. [[Alfred Vohrer]], 1973) \u2014 based on a novel by [[Johannes Mario Simmel]]\n* ''[[Three Men in the Snow (1974 film)|Three Men in the Snow]]'' (dir. [[Alfred Vohrer]], 1974) \u2014 based on a novel by [[Erich K\u00e4stner]]\n* ''[[One or the Other of Us]]'' (dir. [[Wolfgang Petersen]], 1974) \u2014 based on a novel by {{Ill|Horst Bosetzky|de}}\n* ''[[Only the Wind Knows the Answer]]'' (dir. [[Alfred Vohrer]], 1975) \u2014 based on a novel by [[Johannes Mario Simmel]]\n* ''[[To the Bitter End]]'' (dir. [[Gerd Oswald]], 1975) \u2014 based on a novel by [[Johannes Mario Simmel]]\n* ''[[Lili Marleen (film)|Lili Marleen]]'' (dir. [[Rainer Werner Fassbinder]], 1981)\n* ''{{Ill|Crazy Jungle Adventure|de|Im Dschungel ist der Teufel los}}'' (dir. [[Harald Reinl]], 1982)\n* ''{{Ill|Wie h\u00e4tten Sie\u2019s denn gern?|de}}'' (dir. [[Rolf von Sydow]], 1983)\n* ''{{Ill|K\u00f6nig der letzten Tage|de}}'' (dir. {{Ill|Tom Toelle|de}}, 1993, TV film)\n\n===Director===\n* ''[[The Net (1975 film)|The Net]]'' (1975) \u2014 based on a novel by [[Hans Habe]]\n* ''{{ill|The Elixirs of the Devil (1976 film)|de|3=Die Elixiere des Teufels (1976)|lt=The Elixirs of the Devil}}'' (1976) \u2014 based on ''[[The Devil's Elixirs]]'' by [[E. T. A. Hoffmann]]\n* ''[[The Man in the Rushes]]'' (1978) \u2014 based on a novel by {{Ill|George Saiko|de}}\n* ''{{ill|Randale (film)|de|3=Randale (Film)|lt=Randale}}'' (1983)\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|0701050|Manfred Purzer}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Purzer, Manfred}}\n[[Category:1931 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:German screenwriters]]\n[[Category:German film directors]]\n[[Category:German-language film directors]]\n[[Category:German male writers]]\n[[Category:Male screenwriters]]\n\n\n{{Screen-writer-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|German screenwriter}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| image        =\n| name         = Manfred Purzer\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|1931|4|13|df=yes}}\n| birth_place  = [[Munich]], Germany\n| death_date   =\n| death_place  =\n| occupation   = [[Screenwriter]]<br>[[Film director]]\n| yearsactive  = 1955-1993\n}}\n\n'''Manfred Purzer''' (born 13 April 1931) is a German [[screenwriter]] and [[film director]]. He wrote 27 films between 1955 and 1993. In 1974, he was a member of the jury at the [[24th Berlin International Film Festival]].<ref name=\"berlinale\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.berlinale.de/en/archiv/jahresarchive/1974/04_jury_1974/04_Jury_1974.html |title=Berlinale 1974: Juries |accessdate=2 July 2010 |work=berlinale.de}}</ref>\n\n==Selected filmography==\n===Screenwriter===\n* ''{{ill|Komm nur, mein liebstes V\u00f6gelein|de}}'' (dir. [[Rolf Thiele]], 1968) \u2014 based on a book by {{Ill|Joachim Fernau|de}}\n* ''[[Seven Days Grace]]'' (dir. [[Alfred Vohrer]], 1969) \u2014 based on a novel by {{Ill|Paul Henricks|de}}\n* ''{{Ill|Herzblatt oder Wie sag ich\u2019s meiner Tochter?|de}}'' (dir. [[Alfred Vohrer]], 1969)\n* ''[[The Sex Nest]]'' (dir. [[Alfred Vohrer]], 1970) \u2014 based on a novel by {{Ill|Bengta Bischoff|de}}\n* ''{{Ill|Perrak|de}}'' (dir. [[Alfred Vohrer]], 1970)\n* ''{{ill|Die Weibchen|de}}'' (dir. [[Zbyn\u011bk Brynych]], 1970)\n* ''[[Und Jimmy ging zum Regenbogen]]'' (dir. [[Alfred Vohrer]], 1971) \u2014 based on a novel by [[Johannes Mario Simmel]]\n* ''{{ill|Der neue hei\u00dfe Sex-Report \u2013 Was M\u00e4nner nicht f\u00fcr m\u00f6glich halten|de}}'' (dir. [[Ernst Hofbauer]], 1971)\n* ''[[Love Is Only a Word]]'' (dir. [[Alfred Vohrer]], 1971) \u2014 based on a novel by [[Johannes Mario Simme